# memorizer-app — Android debug build & emulator install

## Use this workflow (what works)

From `artifacts/memorizer-app`, with emulator running (`adb devices` shows `device`):

```bash
export JAVA_HOME="/Applications/Android Studio.app/Contents/jbr/Contents/Home"
export ANDROID_HOME="$HOME/Library/Android/sdk"
export PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:$ANDROID_HOME/platform-tools:$PATH"

cd artifacts/memorizer-app
pnpm dlx node@24 ./node_modules/expo/bin/cli run:android
```

- Builds native code + installs APK on the connected emulator.
- Starts Metro on port 8081 (debug is a **dev client** — JS loads from Metro, not only the APK).
- Do **not** pass `--no-bundler` unless Metro is already running.

After install, if the app can't reach Metro:

```bash
adb reverse tcp:8081 tcp:8081
adb shell am start -n com.verbitra.app/.MainActivity
```

APK output: `artifacts/memorizer-app/android/app/build/outputs/apk/debug/app-debug.apk`

## Avoid these mistakes

| Don't | Why |
|-------|-----|
| `cd android && ./gradlew assembleDebug` alone | Often **UP-TO-DATE** (stale APK); debug skips JS embed by default |
| `./gradlew clean assembleDebug` | **Fails** on this repo — `clean` removes React Native codegen JNI dirs CMake needs |
| Start a second Metro on 8081 | Port already in use; `expo run:android` starts Metro |
| `expo run:android --device emulator-5554` | Expo expects AVD **name**, not `adb` serial — omit `--device` if one emulator is connected |

## Standalone APK (no Metro)

User must ask explicitly. Use release signing (`keystore.properties` exists) or EAS — not the default debug dev-client flow.

## Prerequisites

- Android Studio JBR for `JAVA_HOME` (system Java may be missing).
- Emulator running before `run:android`.
